The paper deals with an online buffer management problem in a switch, which is a classic problem in computer science. The problem involves optimizing the profit gained by transmitting packets with specific release times, deadlines, and values. The paper proposes an algorithm with a matching competitive ratio for the 2-bounded model with lookahead. This problem is related to data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), algorithms (cs.AL), and game theory (cs.GT).
